 Chelsea secured their first win under new manager Thomas Tuchel with a 2-0 win over Burnley in the Premier at the Stamford Bridge on Sunday afternoon. Goals from Cesar Azpilicueta in the first and a second half goal from Marcos Alonso ensured Chelsea grabbed their first win under the manager that replaced sacked Frank Lampard. Chelsea was the better side of the day, the Blues had 71% ball possession, 19 goal attempts though the home team was wasteful in front of goal, they had eight shots on goal, nine shots off goal and two blocked shots in the entire match. Post Views: 
